# Add patterns of files dvc should ignore, which could improve
# the performance. Learn more at
# https://dvc.org/doc/user-guide/dvcignore
# 1. Ignore everything in the project globally
*

# 2. UN-EXCLUDE (Re-include) the DVC-required files
!.dvcignore
!dvc.yaml
!.gitignore

# 3. UN-EXCLUDE the data and model folders to allow DVC to look inside
!data/
!model/

# 4. Exclude all contents inside data/ and model/ (re-applying the filter)
data/*
model/*

# 5. UN-EXCLUDE specific file types inside the data/ and model/ folders
# Use !**/*.ext to ensure deep files are caught, or use the direct path if only checking the top level
!data/**/*.csv
!data/**/*.json
!data/**/*.pkl

!model/**/*.csv
!model/**/*.json
!model/**/*.pkl